SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1244
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Jackson Simmons on
being named the Johnson City Press/Kingsport
Times News Tri-Cities Boys' Basketball Player of
the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should recognize those incredibly successful student
athletes who have distinguished themselves as inspirational leaders among their peers; and
WHEREAS, Jackson Simmons, a senior at Unicoi County High School, was recently
named the Johnson City Press/Kingsport Times News Tri-Cities Boys' Basketball Player of the
Year based upon his outstanding performance on the hardwood this season; and
WHEREAS, Jackson Simmons was the very epitome of consistency for the Blue Devils
during the 2025-2026 season, shooting 62% from the field and averaging 25.5 points, 2 assists,
and 5 rebounds per game; and
WHEREAS, the all-time leading scorer in Unicoi County High School history, Mr.
Simmons finished his career with 2,823 points and currently ranks fourth on the Northeast
Tennessee boys' basketball all-time scoring list; and
WHEREAS, Jackson Simmons exemplifies the spirit, determination, and perseverance
for which Tennesseans are notable, and he is richly deserving of our approbation on this special
occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Jackson Simmons of
Unicoi County High School upon being named Tri-Cities Boys' Basketball Player of the Year
and extend to him our best wishes for every continued success on the court and in life.
